results.name: a(n) is the number of partitions of n into 2 positive cubes.
comment: In other words, number of solutions to the equation x^3 + y^3 = n with x >= y > 0. - _Antti Karttunen_, Aug 28 2017
The first term > 1 is a(1729) = 2. - _Michel Marcus_, Apr 23 2019
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..100000
Index entries for sequences related to sums of cubes
formula: If a(n) > 0 then A025456(n + k^3) > 0 for k>0; a(A113958(n)) > 0; a(A003325(n)) > 0. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jun 03 2006
a(n) = [x^n y^2] Product_{k>=1} 1/(1 - y*x^(k^3)). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Apr 23 2019
xref: Cf. A025456, A025468, A003108, A003325, A000578, A048766, A001235 (two or more ways, positions where a(n) > 1).
